The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 EU Iran offer 

 Brussels, May 15 (Reuters): The EU said today it was prepared to share the most advanced civilian nuclear technology with Iran if it did not have other atomic ambitions. 

 EU foreign policy chief Javier Solana said a planned EU offer of incentives would go beyond a package of sweeteners rejected by Tehran last year. 

 Volcano ash 

 Mount Merapi, Indonesia (AP): Clouds of deadly hot ash, rock fragments and volcanic gas surged down Merapis slopes on Monday, as activity at the mountain intensified to its highest level yet. 

 Brazil clashes 

 Sao Paulo, Brazil (Reuters): Gangsters set buses ablaze and shot up banks in Brazils business capital Sao Paulo overnight in a campaign of violence in which over 70 people have been killed in three days. 

 Germany race 

 Berlin (Reuters): Attacks on foreigners in Germany are on the increase, a lobby group said on Monday, just weeks before thousands of soccer fans and players head to the country for the World Cup. 




